txt.en: 'Hold 'em down, maggots! I'll give 'em two between the eyes for Gorgar!'
Órug can be found at Drenghól in the War of Three Peaks.\n\nYou have defeated lieutenants Ogarbuk, Bauzmát, and Gádhmal at Bagûd-mekhem. You should report to Órug.
Lieutenants Ogarbuk, Bauzmát, and Gádhmal can be found at Bagûd-mekhem.\n\nAfter learning of their arrival at Bagûd-mekhem, Órug has asked you to defeat the lieutenants of Gorgar.
In an effort to overcome the dwarves of the Gabil'akkâ, Gorgar has sent three of his mightiest lieutenants to oversee his forces at Bagûd-mekhem.

'[placeholder], I have received word that Gorgar has bolstered his presence at Bagûd-mekhem.

'It seems three of Gorgar's most trustworthy lieutenants have been sent to oversee his forces and lead a new front against the Gabil'akkâ. It remains unclear if Gorgar is even aware of the alliance between his forces and the small contingent of the Frost-horde gathered within Bagûd-mekhem.

'If there are troubles between them, so be it. Nevertheless, the defeat of his lieutenants is of utmost importance!'
'You've gone far enough, worm! Gorgar wants your head!'
'It is done? Good!\n\n'Let that be a lesson to Gorgar and his Orcs!'
